    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="759"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2156.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Chargé d’Affaires ad
                            interim</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of Mexico</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1911</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1560.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to apply to the
                    Department under your excellency’s most worthy charge with a request that it be
                    pleased to use its good offices to the effect that the proper authorities of San
                    Pedro, Cal., will arrange to thwart the maneuvers of the Magonist junta at Los
                    Angeles toward sending expeditions from that place to Lower California.</p>
                <p>Thanking your excellency in advance for the orders you may be pleased to issue in
                    furtherance of this request,</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carlos Pereyra.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
